{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2016}} [[File:Norwegian-bible-belt.png|thumb|Rough indication of the Norwegian Bible Belt.]] [[File:Kristelig Folkeparti Stortingsvalg 2017.svg|thumb|Support for the Christian Democratic Party at the 2017 parliamentary election.]] {{For|the Bible Belt in other countries|Bible Belt}} The '''Norwegian Bible Belt''' (Norwegian: ''bibelbeltet'') is a loosely defined southwestern coastal area of [[Norway]], which is more religious than most of Norway.<ref name="ESP">{{Cite episode |url=http://theesp.eu/podcast_archive/episode_021_marit_m_simonsen.html |title=Episode No. 021, feat. Marit M. Simonsen |last=Pintér |first=András |last2=Levin |first2=Jelena |last3=Böckman |first3=Pontus |series=The [[European Skeptics Podcast]] |number=21 |format=podcast |date=7 May 2016 |accessdate=17 May 2016}} {{rp|at=54:30}}</ref> Typically, the definition covers [[Western Norway]] (Vestlandet) and [[Southern Norway]] (Sørlandet), which includes the [[Counties of Norway|counties]] of [[Rogaland]] (typically called the "buckle" of the Bible Belt), [[Hordaland]], [[Sogn og Fjordane]], [[Møre og Romsdal]], [[Vest-Agder]] and [[Aust-Agder]].<ref name="Fitjar">{{Cite book |last=Fitjar |first=Rune Dahl |date=2009 |title=The Rise of Regionalism: Causes of Regional Mobilization in Western Europe |url=https://books.google.nl/books?id=GvqMAgAAQBAJ&pg=PT164 |location=[[Abingdon-on-Thames|Abingdon]] |publisher=Routledge |page=164–5 |isbn=9781135203290 |accessdate=17 May 2016}}</ref><ref name="Vincett">{{Cite book |last1=Vincett |first1=Giselle |last2=Obinna |first2=Elijah |date=2014 |title=Christianity in the Modern World: Changes and Controversies |url=https://books.google.nl/books?id=LK1IBQAAQBAJ&pg=PA158 |location=Farnham |publisher=[[Ashgate Publishing]] |page=158 |isbn=9781409470250 |accessdate=17 May 2016}}</ref> However, the most urban areas, such as [[Stavanger]] (once known as the 'religious capital of Norway'), have become strongly [[secularisation|secularised]] since the 1960s and are no longer considered part of the Bible Belt.<ref name="Fitjar"/>
== Characteristics == Socioeconomic [[gender equality]] in the Bible Belt is the lowest in all of Norway; the major cities of [[Bergen]], Stavanger and [[Kristiansand]], however, are amongst the most progressive municipalities in the country.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.dagen.no/Innenriks/Minst_likestilling_i_Bibelbeltet-17755 |title=Minst likestilling i Bibelbeltet |work=[[Dagen (Norwegian newspaper)|Dagen]] |date=21 February 2011 |accessdate=17 May 2016 |language=no}}</ref> In the 1926 referendum on the repeal of prohibition on alcohol, the Bible Belt cast a strong vote against repeal (73.1% in Rogaland, 77.2% in Møre og Romsdal), unlike the rest of Norway.<ref name="Fitjar"/> The Bible Belt also has a strong [[pietist]] movement, that opposes the central authority of the State [[Church of Norway]]. Rogaland is home to many missionary associations and the strongest base of the two main [[Christian democracy|Christian democratic]] parties, the [[Moderate Liberal Party|Moderate Left]] and [[Christian Democratic Party (Norway)|Christian People's Party]] (the latter originally being from Hordaland).<ref name="Fitjar"/><ref>{{Cite book |last=David |first=Arter |date=2013 |title=Scandinavian politics today |url=https://books.google.nl/books?id=8f7HCgAAQBAJ&pg=PT138 |location=Oxford |publisher=Oxford University Press |page=138 |isbn=9781847794932 |accessdate=19 May 2016}}</ref> In Sørlandet, Sunday [[church attendance]] is observed by 2 in 10 people, compared to slightly less than 1 in 10 in Norway on average.<ref name="Vincett"/>
Aust-Agder, Vest-Agder and Rogaland have the highest percentage of married farmers, and the lowest percentage of cohabitants. Rogaland and Sogn og Fjordane have the lowest proportion of divorces and [[Marital separation|separations]], and the latter country also has the highest rate of unmarried farmers. According to research institute Forskning.no this relationship pattern is typical of the Bible Belt.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.nrk.no/troms/bonderomatikk-pa-bygda-1.7052672 |title=Bonderomatikk på bygda |author=Robert Greiner |work=[[NRK]] |date=24 March 2010 |accessdate=19 May 2016 |language=no}}</ref>
== Little Bible Belt == There is also a "Little Bible Belt" (''lille bibelbeltet'') in the southeast near the Swedish border, covering [[Rømskog]], [[Marker, Norway|Marker]] and [[Aremark]].{{cn|date=May 2016}}
