{{Status of religious freedom}} '''Freedom of religion in Brazil''' is a constitutionally protected right, allowing believers the freedom to [[Freedom of assembly|assemble]] and [[worship]] without limitation or interference. Non-traditional religions are well tolerated in the Brazilian culture.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pge.sp.gov.br/centrodeestudos/revistaspge/revista2/artigo5.htm|title=O DIREITO DE RELIGIAO NO BRASIL|website=www.pge.sp.gov.br}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://aocr92.jusbrasil.com.br/artigos/247529335/o-exercicio-da-liberdade-religiosa-no-brasil|title=O Exercício da Liberdade Religiosa no Brasil|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://istoe.com.br/152980_O+NOVO+RETRATO+DA+FE+NO+BRASIL/|title=O novo retrato da fé no Brasil - ISTOÉ Independente|date=19 August 2011|publisher=}}</ref>
