'''Hieromneme''' ({{IPAc-en|ˌ|h|aɪər|ɒ|m|ˈ|n|iː|m|iː}}; [[Ancient Greek]]: Ἱερομνημη) was a minor [[naiad]] of Asia Minor in [[Greek mythology]]. She was a daughter of the river-god [[Simoeis|Simoïs]] and the wife of [[Assaracus]], by whom she bore [[Capys]].<ref>''[[Bibliotheca (Pseudo-Apollodorus)|Bibliotheca]]'' 3. 12. 2</ref> Alternately, she was the daughter-in-law of Assaracus, wife of Capys and mother of [[Anchises]].<ref>[[Dionysius of Halicarnassus]], ''Roman Antiquities'', 1. 62. 2. According to Apollodorus, the mother of Anchises by Capys was [[Themiste]].</ref>

Hieromneme's means "memory of the holy rites" from the Greek words ''hieros'' and ''mnêma.''

