PTICS CONFERENCE |author=John Hartevelt |work=[[The Press]] |publisher=[[Fairfax Media]] |date=24 September 2007 }}</ref> |- | [[Northeast Conference on Science and Skepticism]] (NECSS) || 2009 || [[New York City]] || {{USA}} || Organised by New York City Skeptics, [[New England Skeptical Society]] & Society for Science-Based Medicine.<ref name="About NECSS">{{Cite web |url=http://necss.org/about/ |title=About NECSS |work=NECSS website |publisher=NECSS |accessdate=11 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://necss.org/2014/11/20/save-the-date-for-necss-2015/ |title=Save the date for NECSS 2015 |work=NECSS website |publisher=NECSS |date=28 November 2014 |accessdate=11 March 2015}}</ref> 400 attendees.<ref name="About NECSS"/> |- | [[QED (conference)|QED: Question, Explore, Discover]] || 2011 || [[Manchester]], [[England]] || {{UK}} || Organised by the [[Merseyside Skeptics Society]] and the Greater Manchester Skeptics Society. 650 attendees (2016).<ref name="Skepter">{{Cite journal |last=Korteweg |first=Leon |date=2 December 2016 |title=QED 2016 – verslag van een lang weekend tussen skeptici |url=https://kloptdatwel.nl/2016/12/02/verslag-qed-2016/ |journal=[[Skepter]] |publisher=[[Stichting Skepsis]] |volume=29 |issue=4 |pages=45–46 |accessdate=21 October 2017 |language=nl}}</ref> |- | SkepchickCON || 2009<ref>{{cite web|title=SkepchickCON 2009 Announcement|url=http://skepchick.org/2008/12/announcing-skepchick-con-2009/|website=skepchick.org|accessdate=14 May 2015}}</ref> || [[Bloomington,_Minnesota|Bloomington]], [[Minnesota (U.S. state)|Minnesota]] || {{USA}} ||The scientific skepticism track at [[CONvergence]], a 4-day science fiction and fantasy conference held annually in Bloomington Minnesota on the first full weekend in July. |- | SkepKon (GWUP-Konferenz) || 1987 || Various<ref name="SkepKon">GWUP conferences have been held in various cities in Germany, except the 2011 conference in Vienna, Austria.</ref> || {{GER}}<ref name="SkepKon"/> || Sponsored by the