'''Lucio Ángel Vallejo Balda''' (born [[Villamediana de Iregua]], [[Logroño]], [[Spain]], 12 June 1961) is a [[Holy See|Vatican]] [[monsignor]] who was jailed for [[Leak (media)|leaking]] official documents in the [[Vatileaks]] scandal.<ref name="Pope grants">{{cite news | url= http://www.foxnews.com/world/2016/12/20/pope-grants-freedom-to-jailed-prelate-in-leaks-scandal.html | title= Pope grants freedom to jailed prelate in leaks scandal | publisher= ''[[Fox News]]'' | date= December 20, 2016 | accessdate= }}</ref><ref name="Pope frees">{{cite news | url= https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-38386647 | title= Pope frees jailed priest who leaked official documents | publisher= [[BBC News]] | date= 20 December 2016 | accessdate= }}</ref><ref name="Pope frees Vatican">{{cite news | url= http://www.cbsnews.com/news/pope-francis-vatican-monsignor-lucio-vallejo-balda-christmas-clemency/ | title= Pope frees Vatican monsignor convicted of leaking confidential documents | publisher= [[CBS News]] | date= December 20, 2016 | accessdate= }}</ref> The clergyman admitted to passing classified documents to journalists.<ref name="Stephanie Kirchgaessner">{{cite news | last= Kirchgaessner | first= Stephanie | url= https://www.theguardian.com/world/2016/mar/14/monsignor-lucio-vallejo-balda-vatican-leak-trial | title= Clergyman admits he gave classified Vatican documents to journalists | publisher= ''[[The Guardian]]'' | date= 14 March 2016 | accessdate= }}</ref> He is highest-ranking [[Holy See|Vatican]] official ever to be arrested.<ref name="Shawn Tully">{{cite news | last= Tully | first= Shawn | url= http://fortune.com/2015/11/16/vatican-leak-pope-francis/ | title= Why Would a Highly Respected Vatican Official Turn into a Vati-Leaker? | publisher= ''[[Fortune (magazine)|Fortune]]'' | date= November 16, 2015 | accessdate= }}</ref> [[Pope Francis]] granted him [[clemency]] after he served half of the 18-month jail sentence.<ref name="Pope frees" />
